article.description: Marshawn Wilson scored 17 points on 6 of 8 shooting to help lead Northern Illinois to a 100-52 victory over Division III Eureka College on Saturday.
article.headline: Northern Illinois has no trouble with Eureka in 100-52 win
article.linkText: Northern Illinois has no trouble with Eureka in 100-52 win
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. -- Marshawn Wilson scored 17 points on 6 of 8 shooting to help lead Northern Illinois to a 100-52 victory over Division III Eureka College on Saturday. Chuks Iroegbu finished with 12 points on 5 of 6 shooting and Jaylen Key added 12 more on 5 of 9 from the field for the Huskies (4-0), who are on a four game winning streak to begin the year. Northern Illinois shot 53.4 percent from the field, 88.2 percent at the free throw line, and dished out 32 total assists, including a game-high 10 from Laytwan Porter. The Huskies opened on a 12-0 run, highlighted by an Iroegbu dunk and 3-point play, and never trailed in the game. They led 58-25 at the half and a Jordan Thomas 3 with 3:56 left pushed the lead past 40. Hank Thomas had 13 points for Eureka.
